	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000579_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p>I enclose a letter for <persName>Robert</persName> which I wrote on the 
<lb/><placeName>Molopo</placeName>, if it will do address it If not tell me &amp; 
<lb/>I shall try &amp; write a better =<!-- equals sign????--> I have my answer to 
<lb/><persName>Mr Edwards</persName> letter open, the other to the Directors 
<lb/>was written on the <placeName>Molopo</placeName> &amp; may be sent off immediately 
<lb/>If you think it ought to be sent now they may both go together</p>
<lb/><p><!-- addresses etc written accross bottom of page - different hands-->Livingston</p>
<lb/><p><placeName>Mabot<supplied resp="#CO">sa</supplied><!--add sa--></placeName></p>
<lb/><p>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April 1845</p><!--different hand--><!-- <p>Autograph</p>
<p>of D. Livingston</p>-->
<lb/><p><persName>R M <!--correct ??? Robert Moffat--></persName></p>
<lb/><p><!-- other way round address, Livingstone hand???-->R. Moffat</p>
<lb/><p><placeName>Kuruman</placeName></p>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000579_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<!--Hand 01 3 top left--><!--Hand 02 68213 top right--><!--Hand 03 1/4/1845 top right-->
<lb/><p><term type="reference">Richardson's dictionary</term>, the hamper in which 
<lb/>the apples were, and sail cloth bag in which the 
<lb/>bed was rolled up. If anything else was to go 
<lb/>back we have forgot but should it occur to 
<lb/>us we shall return it by first opportunity 
<lb/>If <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Hume</persName> could sell us one of his mills 
<lb/>we should be glad, for we have both wheat &amp; 
<lb/>maize we could grind. We have excellent 
<lb/>potatoes but a worm plagues them &amp; kills 
<lb/>large plants. What will destroy them? 
<lb/><persName>Cornelius</persName> came &amp; spoke to me about his soul on 
<lb/>saturday last. He seemed much affected, I wished he 
<lb/>had gone out straight to you. When he does come 
<lb/>you will remember him.<!--Hand 04 signed D & M Livingstone--> Sign<hi rend="sup">d</hi><!--is this right????--> D. &amp; M. Livingstone</p>
			
